#   POST-017: a refused/failed `be post` is non-atomic ŌĆö writes the reflog before the objects are safely stored

A `be post` that is REFUSED (or errors) after it has begun can still leave a
`post` row in the store reflog (`<store>/<shard>/refs`) and a `put` staging row,
even though NO commit object was created. The reflog/refs write must be the LAST
step ŌĆö `be post` may append the reflog row ONLY after the commit objects are safely
in the store: written, `msync`'d (durably flushed), AND indexed. Any refusal/error
before that point must leave the reflog (and staging) UNCHANGED ŌĆö the post is
all-or-nothing. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Repro (2026-06-16, landing BLAME-006b): `be post` was refused by `POSTCFLCT`
    (the [[POST-006]] marker-string false positive on `graf/WEAVE.c`), yet it had
    ALREADY appended a stray row to the shared store reflog
    (`/home/gritzko/beagle/.be/dogs/refs`: `26616Cpe5S post ?#f6bea1c5ŌĆ”`, a duplicate
    of the parent row) and staged an `abc` gitlink ŌĆö while creating NO commit. `be
    head` still resolved the true tip (refs are sha-lineage, not row-order), so it is
    harmless to resolution, but it is debris that accumulates and reads like a tip.
 -  Root: the refs/reflog (and staging) write happens BEFORE the commit is finalized,
    so a late refusal (conflict scan) or any error after that write but before the
    commit leaves the partial row behind. A post is not all-or-nothing.
 -  Cousin of [[GET-018]] (atomic wt GET) ŌĆö same "stage/commit-point ordering so a
    mid-op failure leaves nothing changed" shape, on the POST side.

### Goals
 -  `be post` writes the reflog row as the FINAL, single commit point ŌĆö only after the
    commit object(s) are (1) written to the store, (2) `msync`'d to durable storage,
    and (3) indexed (`.refs.idx` / graf / spot). Before that point, a refusal/error
    (POSTCFLCT, validation, transport, crash) leaves the reflog and staging UNCHANGED.
 -  No stray/duplicate refs rows or orphan `put` staging from a refused post.

### Constraints
 -  Move ALL validation that can refuse a post (notably the `POSTCFLCT` conflict scan)
    BEFORE any reflog/staging mutation, so a refusal never reaches the write.
 -  Don't regress the legitimate post path or the documented `--force` conflict-scan
    bypass; output and landed-commit shape unchanged on the happy path.
 -  Store writes only ŌĆö keep the wtlog/refs/index ordering consistent with [[GET-018]].

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  ROOT CAUSE (scan done 2026-06-16) ŌĆö the premise was half-right: the leak is NOT the
    `refs`/reflog text row (that REFS write at ~`sniff/POST.c:3080` runs AFTER the scan, so
    it was untouched), it is ORPHAN OBJECTS + a rewritten INDEX. The `POSTCFLCT` scan ran
    MID-pack-feed (`sniff/POST.c:3012-3022`), inside the blob-feed loop, AFTER `KEEPPackOpen`
    (~`POST.c:2745`) and after all trees were fed; on a hit it called `KEEPPackClose`, which
    PERSISTS the pack, publishes a fresh idx puppy (`keep_pup_create_next`) and runs
    `KEEPCompact` (`keeper/KEEP.c:1782-1851`), THEN returned POSTCFLCT ŌĆö so a refusal left
    orphan tree+blob objects in `0000000001.keeper` and a rewritten `*.keeper.idx` durably.
    (The earlier observed stray `26616Cpe5S` refs row was a SEPARATE partial op, not this.)
 -  FIX: hoist ALL refuse-capable validation to a pre-flight (step 5a, `POST.c:2675`), right
    after `post_scan_changeset` builds the decisions ULOG and BEFORE the unlink/`KEEPPackOpen`/
    any object/index/reflog write. New `post_cflct_scan_cb` (`POST.c:1240`) reads each `add`
    row's wt body (same mmap/readlink idiom as the feed loop) + `SNIFFHasConflictMarker`; a hit
    returns POSTCFLCT before any store mutation. Removed the redundant in-loop scan. `--force`
    skips the pre-flight exactly as before.

